{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"init_","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"CancellableT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CancellableT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO19CancellableProtocolP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol","text":"CancellableProtocol","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This method is intended for language bindings. If writing in C,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_initable_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" should typically be used instead."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The object must be initialized before any real use after initial"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"construction, either with this function or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_async_initable_init_async()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementations may also support cancellation. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then initialization can be cancelled by triggering the cancellable object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from another thread. If the operation was cancelled, the error","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be returned. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" is not ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the object doesn’t support cancellable initialization the error"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notSupported"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the object is not initialized, or initialization returns with an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"error, then all operations on the object except ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_unref()"},{"type":"text","text":" are considered to be invalid, and have undefined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"behaviour. See the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for more details."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Callers should not assume that a class which implements ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"initialized multiple times, unless the class explicitly documents itself as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"supporting this. Generally, a class’ implementation of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init()"},{"text":" can assume","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(and assert) that it will only be called once. Previously, this documentation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recommended all ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable"},{"type":"text","text":" implementations should be idempotent; that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recommendation was relaxed in GLib 2.54.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a class explicitly supports being initialized multiple times, it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recommended that the method is idempotent: multiple calls with the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"arguments should return the same results. Only the first call initializes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the object; further calls return the result of the first call."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"One reason why a class might need to support idempotent initialization is if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it is designed to be used via the singleton pattern, with a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"GObjectClass.constructor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that sometimes returns an existing instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In this pattern, a caller would expect to be able to call "},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the result of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_new()"},{"text":", regardless of whether it is in fact a new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/initableprotocol\/init_(cancellable:)-5fjh8"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"init_(cancellable:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"init_","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"CancellableT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CancellableT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"extendedModule":"GIO","externalID":"s:3GIO16InitableProtocolPAAE5init_11cancellableSbqd__Sg_tKAA011CancellableC0Rd__lF"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol\/init_(cancellable:)-5fjh8"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface."}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableProtocol":{"role":"symbol","title":"CancellableProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CancellableProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GCancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Initable":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/initable","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Initable","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Initable","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" is implemented by objects that can fail during"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initialization. If an object implements this interface then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it must be initialized as the first thing after construction,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"either via [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Initable.init"},{"text":"] or [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.init_async"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(the latter is only available if it also implements [iface","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Initable"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/AsyncInitable":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","title":"AsyncInitable","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/asyncinitable","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"code":"GAsyncInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface for asynchronously initializable objects."}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InitableProtocol/init_(cancellable:)-5fjh8":{"title":"init_(cancellable:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface."}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/initableprotocol\/init_(cancellable:)-5fjh8","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"init_","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"CancellableT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableT"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol\/init_(cancellable:)-5fjh8","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InitableProtocol":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/initableprotocol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"code":"GInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is implemented by objects that can fail during","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"initialization. If an object implements this interface then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it must be initialized as the first thing after construction,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"either via [method"},{"code":"Gio.Initable.init","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] or [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.init_async"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(the latter is only available if it also implements [iface","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InitableProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"InitableProtocol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InitableProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"#iface@Gio.Initable#description":{"type":"link","title":"description","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"description","type":"text"}],"identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","url":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description"}}}